claim: As visible in Figure 1 and Table S4, Supplemental Digital Content, http://links.lww.com/PSYMED/B18, the PHQ-15 g-factor was not significantly correlated with ER or with g-valence or g-arousal.
title: FIGURE 1.
caption: Structural equation model with the bifactor PHQ and emotion regulation strategies. Note. Only significant correlations are shown. Double-headed arrows depict correlations, whereas single-headed arrows depict factor loadings of latent variables. Red arrows indicate negative relationships. PHQ = Patient Health Questionnaire. Color image is available online only at the journal website.
